In[2]:
def readAudio(fileName):
    rate, data = wav.read(fileName)
    return rate, data

def plotWaveform(rate, data, title):
    time = np.arange(0, len(data)) / rate

    zoomStart = int(rate * 2)
    zoomEnd = zoomStart + int(rate * 0.025)

    if (title == "WLow.wav" or title == "WHigh.wav"):
        zoomStart = int(rate * 0.5)
        zoomEnd = zoomStart + int(rate * 0.0035)

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 4))

    plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
    plt.plot(time, data)
    plt.title(title)
    plt.xlabel("Time (seconds)")
    plt.ylabel("Amplitude")

    plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
    plt.plot(time[zoomStart:zoomEnd], data[zoomStart:zoomEnd])
    plt.title(f"{title} - Zoomed In")
    plt.xlabel("Time (seconds)")
    plt.ylabel("Amplitude")

    plt.show()

import numpy as np
from scipy.signal import correlate, find_peaks
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from scipy.io import wavfile

def crossCorrelate(reference, signal):
    reference = (reference - np.mean(reference)) / (np.std(reference) * len(reference))
    signal = (signal - np.mean(signal)) / np.std(signal)
    return correlate(signal, reference, mode='valid')

def readAudio(filename):
    rate, data = wavfile.read(filename)
    if len(data.shape) > 1:
        data = data[:, 0]
    return rate, data

rateA, dataA = readAudio("./sounds/OLow.wav")
rateE, dataE = readAudio("./sounds/erozijaSlow.wav")

assert rateA == rateE, "Sample rates must be equal"

vowelDuration = 0.2
samples = int(vowelDuration * rateA)
trimmedA = dataA[:samples]

correlation = crossCorrelate(trimmedA, dataE)

times = np.arange(len(correlation)) / rateE

peaks, _ = find_peaks(correlation, height=0.5*np.max(correlation), distance=int(0.1*rateE))

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
plt.plot(times, correlation, label='Cross-correlation')
plt.plot(peaks/rateE, correlation[peaks], 'ro', label='Detected peaks')
plt.title("Cross-Correlation of 'o' vowel with 'erozija'")
plt.xlabel("Time (s)")
plt.ylabel("Normalized Correlation")
plt.legend()
plt.grid()
plt.show()

print(f"Detected 'o' vowels at times: {peaks/rateE} seconds")

In[6]:
from scipy.signal import find_peaks
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from scipy.io import wavfile

def readAudio(filename):
    rate, data = wavfile.read(filename)
    return rate, data[:, 0] if len(data.shape) > 1 else data

def crossCorrelate(reference, signal):
    refNorm = (reference - np.mean(reference)) / (np.std(reference) + 1e-10)
    sigNorm = (signal - np.mean(signal)) / (np.std(signal) + 1e-10)
    return correlate(sigNorm, refNorm, mode='valid')

def detectVowelPosition(wordFile, vowelFiles, vowelNames):
    rateWord, dataWord = readAudio(wordFile)
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 8))
    
    for vowelFile, vowelName in zip(vowelFiles, vowelNames):
        rateVowel, dataVowel = readAudio(vowelFile)
        assert rateVowel == rateWord, "Sample rates must match"
        if vowelName == 'a':
            vowelDuration = 0.1
        elif vowelName == 'i':
            vowelDuration = 0.4
        elif vowelName == 'o':
            vowelDuration = 0.4
        
        samples = int(vowelDuration * rateVowel)
        trimmedVowel = dataVowel[:samples]
        
        correlation = crossCorrelate(trimmedVowel, dataWord)
        times = np.arange(len(correlation)) / rateWord
        
        peaks, properties = find_peaks(correlation, 
                                     height=0.3*np.max(correlation),
                                     distance=int(0.2*rateWord))
        
        if len(peaks) > 0:
            strongestPeak = peaks[np.argmax(properties['peak_heights'])]
            peaks = [strongestPeak]
        
        plt.plot(times, correlation, label=f'Correlation with {vowelName}')
        if len(peaks) > 0:
            plt.plot(peaks[0]/rateWord, correlation[peaks[0]], 'o', 
                    markersize=10, label=f'Detected {vowelName}')
    
    plt.title("Vowel Detection in Word (Single Strongest Peak)")
    plt.xlabel("Time (s)")
    plt.ylabel("Normalized Correlation")
    plt.legend()
    plt.grid()
    plt.show()

vowelFiles = ["./sounds/ALow.wav", "./sounds/ILow.wav", "./sounds/OLow.wav"]
vowelNames = ['a', 'i', 'o']
detectVowelPosition("./sounds/erozijaSlow.wav", vowelFiles, vowelNames)
